    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-05T17:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-05T17:30:00-05:00" n="659"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.76 Monitoring/500: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Corrigan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-05T18:30:00-04:00"
                            >February 5, 1943—6:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–378. Your 70, January 13, noon.<note n="5" xml:id="d659fn5">Not printed; it
                        reported that Venezuela accepted a plan proposed by the United States to
                        survey and eliminate clandestine radio.</note> Department entirely agreeable
                    that S. R. Lines, Federal Communications Commission engineer who is now in
                    Venezuela shall serve as instructor to Venezuelan technicians in direction
                    finder project for elimination of clandestine radio stations. He will probably
                    remain in Venezuela for 3 months. While entire direction finder project is under
                    your supervision and under the immediate direction of the United States Military
                    Attaché at Caracas, this Government has no objection provided you concur, to
                    ultimate control of Lines’ official activities by Venezuelan authorities. Please
                    appropriately inform Lines.</p>
                <p>Appropriate United States Army officials are being informed with <pb facs="0809"
                        n="795" xml:id="pg_795"/> respect to these requirements as they apply to
                    Army representatives who will proceed to Venezuela in connection with direction
                    finder project.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
